    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Some users are unaware of hot restart and restart the app instead. Are there cases where we could detect when app restarts could be replaced by a hot restart and notify users?\r\n\r\nAlso, users are unaware that pressing the play button again in Android Studio triggers a hot restart when an app is already running.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "A good first step is to use analytics to identify how large a problem this may be. We can track the fraction of users that stop and restart the app and also never run hot reloads from Flutter analytics.\r\nIf this is high, we should consider a message in IntelliJ suggesting using hot restart along with a tip for how to use hot restart any time this pattern of behavior is identified. We could even have this prompt ask users if they were aware of hot restart to fully understand where users are going wrong.\r\n\r\nI believe hot restart is featured more prominently in the VSCode toolbar. \r\nComparing the number of hot restarts from vscode could also clarify this issue.\r\n\r\nFYI @DanTup as VSCode users might also struggle with this.",
            "created_at": "2022-02-17T22:11:34Z",
