            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "In VS Code, we handle the normal Restart button/menu entries as a Hot Restart, so as long as the user is clicking Restart, it'll be a Hot Restart.\r\n\r\nIt could be interesting to set a timer whenever a debug session stops and if another starts within a small period (< 30s?) increment a counter, and if it hits some threshold within a single editor session, show a prompt about hot restart (or solicit feedback on why it's not being used)?",
